---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof for Makeup Artists — Reviews That Build Your Clientele | SocialProof" description="SocialProof helps makeup artists collect client testimonials and embed them on their portfolio or website. Turn happy brides into your best marketing — free to start.">
  <main class="for-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="badge">For Makeup Artists</div>
      <h1>Let Your Clients' Faces Speak for Your Work</h1>
      <p class="subhead">Brides, prom clients, and everyday beauty lovers book makeup artists they trust. SocialProof makes it effortless to collect genuine testimonials and display them on your website — turning happy clients into a steady stream of bookings.</p>
      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-primary">Start free — no credit card</a>
        <a href="/for" class="btn-secondary">See all industries →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pain">
      <h2>The Review Challenge Makeup Artists Face</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Clients love their look in the moment — getting them to write a review later is another story</li>
        <li>Your Instagram shows your work, but testimonials show your professionalism, punctuality, and personality</li>
        <li>Bridal season is your busiest time, but also your worst time to chase follow-ups</li>
        <li>Competing against hundreds of MUAs in your area means social proof is your biggest differentiator</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="solution">
      <h2>How SocialProof Works for Makeup Artists</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Get your collect link</strong> — one permanent link for all your testimonials</li>
        <li><strong>Send it right after an appointment</strong> — text it to the client while they're still glowing</li>
        <li><strong>They submit in under a minute</strong> — no app, no account, just their words</li>
        <li><strong>Approve and embed</strong> — display testimonials on your booking page with one line of code</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="social-proof-for-sp">
      <h2>What Makeup Artists Say About SocialProof</h2>
      <blockquote>
        <p>"I text my collect link right after every session. My clients are still excited — they write the sweetest reviews. My booking page now has 40+ testimonials and my conversion rate is up significantly."</p>
        <cite>— Freelance makeup artist, Los Angeles CA</cite>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        <p>"Brides always ask about my style and process. Having real testimonials from previous brides on my site answers those questions before they even contact me."</p>
        <cite>— Bridal makeup artist, New York NY</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section class="use-cases">
      <h2>Perfect for Every MUA Business Model</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="card"><strong>Bridal MUAs</strong><p>Bridal clients do serious research. A wall of glowing testimonials from previous brides is your most powerful closing tool.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><strong>Freelance artists</strong><p>Build your reputation across multiple platforms. Testimonials on your personal site keep clients coming directly to you.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><strong>Studio owners</strong><p>Collect testimonials for your whole team. Display them by artist or for the studio as a whole.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq">
      <h2>Common Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>When's the best time to send the link?</summary>
        <p>Right after the appointment — within an hour if possible. A quick text while they're admiring their look gets the best response rates. You can also include it in your post-booking confirmation email.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Will this work on my booking site (Square, Vagaro, Squarespace)?</summary>
        <p>Yes — SocialProof embeds with a single script tag on any website builder. If your site allows HTML embeds, SocialProof works.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What does it cost?</summary>
        <p>Free forever for 1 active widget. No credit card needed. Upgrade to Pro ($19/mo) for multiple widgets and advanced styling.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="final-cta">
      <h2>Build the Reputation That Fills Your Calendar</h2>
      <p>Set up your testimonial widget in minutes. Free forever for 1 active widget.</p>
      <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-primary">Get started free</a>
    </section>
  </main>

